{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 15:14:28.246694", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and topology\\n- DC fabric: 1 super-spine (AS 65000), 2 spines (AS 65100/65101), 2 leaves (AS 65200/65201). Hosts: pc_0_0 on leaf_router_0_0 and pc_0_1 on leaf_router_0_1. Host-facing subnets per design: 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 (for pod 0: leaf 0_0 → 10.0.0.0/24, leaf 0_1 → 10.0.1.0/24).\\n\\nKey observations\\n\\n1) Control-plane health (BGP)\\n- All EBGP sessions on leaves, spines, and super-spine are Established with nonzero prefix counts:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 neighbors up; RIB shows 10.0.0.0/24 connected and other leaves’ host subnets learned via BGP.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 neighbors up; RIB shows 10.0.1.0/24 connected and other leaves’ host subnets learned via BGP.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: 6 neighbors each, all up; RIBs contain all expected leaf /24s and ECMP to super-spine for other pods.\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): 8 neighbors up; RIB contains all leaf /24s via spines.\\n- No evidence of BGP flaps, stuck states, or missing routes. Control plane appears healthy and consistent.\\n\\n2) Host configurations and L2/L3 edge\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - IP 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1; ARP neighbor for 10.0.0.1 resolved; ping to 10.0.0.1 succeeds.\\n- pc_0_1:\\n  - IP 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1; ping to 10.0.0.1 fails with “Destination Host Unreachable”; ARP shows 10.0.0.1 FAILED (no neighbor).\\n  - Given topology, the host-facing SVI on leaf_router_0_1 is 10.0.1.1/24 (confirmed on leaf_router_0_1), not 10.0.0.1. Thus pc_0_1 is addressed for the wrong subnet and points to the wrong gateway.\\n\\n3) Reachability tests\\n- Many cross-host pings succeed elsewhere in the fabric, indicating data plane forwarding is generally working.\\n- The test “pc_0_1 → pc_0_0” shows success, but both hosts have the same IP (10.0.0.2). On Linux, pinging your own assigned address is handled locally, yielding a false sense of reachability. This is not end-to-end connectivity and masks the misconfiguration.\\n- “pc_0_1 → 10.0.0.1” fails due to ARP resolution failure, consistent with the wrong L3 domain on pc_0_1.\\n\\nAnomalies detected\\n- Duplicate IP address: pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 are both configured as 10.0.0.2/24.\\n- pc_0_1 is in the wrong L3 subnet and has the wrong default gateway for its attachment:\\n  - Expected per design: leaf_router_0_1’s host subnet is 10.0.1.0/24 with gateway 10.0.1.1.\\n  - Observed: pc_0_1 is configured for 10.0.0.0/24 with gateway 10.0.0.1 (which is on leaf_router_0_0).\\n- Consequence: pc_0_1 cannot ARP its gateway and has no off-link connectivity.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_1 (host).\\n- Network fabric (leaves, spines, super-spine) shows healthy control-plane and correct RIBs; host-facing interfaces on leaves are correctly addressed (10.0.0.1 on leaf_router_0_0; 10.0.1.1 on leaf_router_0_1).\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Host addressing misconfiguration on pc_0_1:\\n  - Incorrect IP and default gateway that do not match the directly connected leaf’s host subnet.\\n  - Duplicate IP conflict with pc_0_0 (both set to 10.0.0.2), leading to misleading “success” when pinging that address from pc_0_1 (local self-ping).\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- pc_0_1 has no functional connectivity to its gateway or any remote networks.\\n- The rest of the fabric appears unaffected and operates normally for other hosts., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a370482e-a1ed-45d0-bb8c-ec73a7afc611'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
